  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the sous-vide machine to 132°F (56°C).",
    "Combine Garlic Powder, Soy Sauce, and Korean Chili Flakes in a mixing bowl.",
    "Add finely chopped onions and finely sliced garlic cloves into the mix with the seasoning mixture. Toss gently.",
    "In a separate pan over medium heat, add oil and sauté thinly sliced carrots until translucent, about 5 minutes.",
    "Once fully cooked, add the seasoned vegetables to the pan, then pour in the watermelon silbets (use only half of them).",
    "Season with freshly ground pepper. Stir fry for another minute or so until everything is warm and well combined.",
    "Serve hot as a meal accompaniment or on its own as a snack."
